Name: Museum of the Weird
Description: As Austin is know as the weird city in Texas. This Museum was created as tribute to Austin. Located in Downtown area on 6th street. The guest will be exposed to a variety of curious and oddities. Some featured objects include bigfoot, three headed pig,  dibbuk, electric man, etc.

Name: Rensselaer Polytechnic Institue
Description: At first glance one may think this is just another private research University. In reality its much more! This is in fact the birth place of Phi Iota Alpha Fraternity, Inc. By definition Phi Iota Alpha is the Oldest Latino Fraternity in Existence who has Alumni who became president of thier country of birth

Name: Alcatraz Island
Description: Famously known as the the U.S. maximum security federal penitentiary. Holding criminals like Al Capone, Roy Gardner to name a few. Nowadays Alcatraz services as a National Park were tourists experience life in the Super Max Federal Pennintary and learn about the Great Escape that is to this day a mystery.

Name: The Queen Mary
Description: When you think about haunted Places one of the names that always comes in mind is the Queen Mary. Stories of Paranomral Activity has continue to amuse toursists throughout the years. Which has lead to the creation of haunted tours of the Qeen Mary.

Name: Los Angeles County Museum of Art
Description: As the Largest Museum in the Western United States. LACMA hold thousands of work that range from Ancient times to contemporary art.  Overall the Museum serves as a mulitcutural center were the public is exposed to so many different culture to increase our understanding of each other.
